The '''Nordic Society for Middle Eastern Studies''' is a [[learned society]] formed in 1989 that is devoted to the promotion of the [[Academia|academic]] study of the [[Middle East]] in the [[Nordic countries|Nordic region]].<ref name="SDU">{{cite web|title=The Tenth Nordic Conference on Middle Eastern Studies|url=http://www.sdu.dk/en/om_sdu/institutter_centre/c_mellemoest/tenthnordicconference|website=University of Southern Denmark|accessdate=22 November 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|editor1-last=Palva|editor1-first=Heikki|editor2-last=Vikør|editor2-first=Knut S.|title=The Middle East — Unity and Diversity|journal=Nordic Proceedings in Asian Studies|volume=5|page=248|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=aluD22J9SG8C&lpg=PA248&ots=r-OOBe2cP9&dq=%22Nordic%20Society%20for%20Middle%20Eastern%20Studies%22&pg=PA248#v=onepage&q=%22Nordic%20Society%20for%20Middle%20Eastern%20Studies%22&f=false|publisher=NIAS Books}}</ref> The Society arranges an [[academic conference]] on Middle Eastern studies, held every three years in a different Nordic country.<ref name="SDU" /><ref>{{cite web|title=Conference|url=http://thenordicsociety.se/conference/|website=The Nordic Society for Middle Eastern Studies|accessdate=22 November 2016}}</ref> The 2016 conference was hosted by the [[University of Southern Denmark]] in [[Odense]].<ref name="SDU" /> The current chairperson of the Nordic Society is [[Leif Stenberg]], who is director of the [[Center for Middle Eastern Studies at Lund University]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Board|url=http://thenordicsociety.se/board/|website=Nordic Society for Middle Eastern Studies|accessdate=22 November 2016}}</ref>

